# Steps to Run Rocky Linux 10.1 vHPC Cluster

## Prerequisites Installation

### Step 1: Install Docker
# macOS:
brew install --cask docker
# Then open Docker Desktop from Applications

# Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
# Log out and back in for group changes to take effect

# Linux (RHEL/CentOS/Rocky):
sudo dnf install -y docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

### Step 2: Verify Docker is Running
docker --version
docker run hello-world

### Step 3: Install Just (Task Runner)
# macOS:
brew install just

# Linux (using cargo):
cargo install just

# Linux (using package manager):
# Ubuntu/Debian - add repository first
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:just/just
sudo apt update
sudo apt install just

# Or download from: https://github.com/casey/just/releases

### Step 4: Verify Just Installation
just --version

### Step 5: Install Ansible (Optional - for cluster configuration)
# macOS:
brew install ansible

# Linux:
sudo dnf install -y ansible    # RHEL/CentOS/Rocky
sudo apt install -y ansible    # Ubuntu/Debian

### Step 6: Verify Ansible Installation
ansible --version

### Step 7: Install Ansible Docker Collection
cd hpc-rocky10
just install-collections

## SSH Key Setup (Required)

### Step 8: Generate SSH Key (if you don't have one)
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f ~/.ssh/id_vhpc -C "vhpc_cluster"
# Press Enter for no passphrase (or set one if preferred)

### Step 9: Verify SSH Key Exists
ls -la ~/.ssh/id_vhpc*

## Build and Start Cluster

### Step 10: View Available Commands
just --list

### Step 12: Build Docker Images
just build
# This takes 5-10 minutes on first build

### Step 13: Start Cluster Containers
just up

### Step 14: Verify Containers are Running
just status
# Should show: lci-head-01, lci-compute-01, lci-compute-02, lci-storage-01

### Step 15: Copy SSH Key to Containers
just copy-ssh-key
# Uses ~/.ssh/id_vhpc.pub by default, or specify: PUBKEY=~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub just copy-ssh-key
# Note: You may be prompted for the rocky user password (Sp@rky26) once during key copy

## Connect to Cluster

### Step 16: SSH into Head Node
# From your host machine:
just ssh rocky
# Or manually:
ssh rocky@localhost -p 2222

# Password for rocky user: Sp@rky26

### Step 17: Elevate to Root (Inside Head Node)
sudo -i
# No password needed - rocky user is in wheel group with NOPASSWD

### Step 18: SSH to Other Nodes (as root from head node)
ssh root@compute-01
ssh root@compute-02
ssh root@storage-01
# No password needed - keys are pre-configured

## Verify Cluster

### Step 19: Check Hostname and Network
hostname
# Should show: head-01

ping compute-01
ping storage-01

### Step 20: Check Installed Software
which tmux nvim vim wget
# All should be available

## Common Tasks

### View Logs
just logs          # All containers
just logs head     # Head node only

### Execute Commands in Container
just exec "hostname"
just exec "dnf list installed"

### Stop Cluster
just down

### Clean Everything (Images, Volumes, Networks)
just clean

### Rebuild and Restart
just build && just up && just copy-ssh-key

## Quick Start (All-in-One)
just setup
# Equivalent to: just build && just up && just copy-ssh-key && just status

## User Credentials
# rocky user password: Sp@rky26 (only needed for initial SSH login)
# root password: root
# sudo from rocky: no password required (wheel group with NOPASSWD)

## Troubleshooting

### SSH Connection Refused
# Ensure containers are running
docker ps

# Check SSH is running in container
docker logs lci-head-01

# Re-run SSH key setup
just copy-ssh-key

### Permission Denied
# Use correct user: ssh rocky@localhost -p 2222
# Password: Sp@rky26

### Docker Not Running
# Start Docker Desktop (macOS) or:
sudo systemctl start docker  # Linux
